=795.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mage pets and summoned armor</span><hr size=1> For a long time now, I've wondered if giving mage pets all this summoned crap we have is benefical.  So last night, along with another lvl 56 mage, we decided to test this concept with two identical lvl 51 Earth pets (the lvl 51 spell Earth pet that is...lol)<br>
<br>
My pet: Lvl 51.  Buffed with BO3. (2) standard daggers for weapons.  Full summoned plate. Elemental Defender.<br>
<br>
Assistants pet: Lvl 51. Buffed with BO3. No weapons or armor whatsoever.<br>
<br>
Result: Nothing. Neither pet had a noticable advantage over the other.<br>
<br>
Conclusion: Pets dont use summoned armor/items except for the MoM.  <br>
<br>
This test was done mutiple times, and the armored pet never showed any indication that it was...umm...well....armored! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 558<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 12:40:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage pets and summoned armor</span><hr size=1> You might want to try it again with lower level pets. <br>
<br>
I believe that summon phantom plate made a huge difference when i first obtained the spell. The effect of the armor has become more and more negligible as I have increased in level.<br>
<br>
This has something to do with the Attack value given to higher level mobs vs. the AC provided by the armor. At lower levels, the AC overpowers the ATK of the mobs. I'm not a melee expert though so I yield the floor at this time..... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 55th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 3:45:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage pets and summoned armor</span><hr size=1> Pets, like other NPCs don't pay any attention to tags on items. You can give two focus rings to a pet for extra AC as well as a summoned choker, a shawl and a pair of summoned earrings. Also if the pet is too low level to dual wield you can give it two elemental defenders, one for back and one for off hand. It's a shame that the muzzle and belts don't have any AC on them. <p><br>
Artulyn Starsummoner Arch Mage<br>
<br>
For the light of a candle to be seen, it must be taken to a dark place. -- UKLG</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirrudn@themagicianstower>Nirrudn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 6:39:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> A few patches back, Verant clearly stated in the patch message that pets do wear armor.<br>
<br>
The specific text I'm talking about says something like &quot;Fixed Emissary of Thule to equip armor and weapons like other pets.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arhallia>Arhallia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 6:57:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   wrong pet</span><hr size=1> Earth pets have AGI under 75.  Giving them armor is almost pointless without an AGI buff to up their AC to reasonable levels to begin with.  Their Atk overpowers their crap AC by such a large margin, giving them 80 AC in armor will make no diff.  You could do the same duel and get a huge difference in outcomes merely by having a shaman AGI buff both pets.<br>
<br>
Try dueling two 54 water pets, one with, one without armor.  Or 53 air pets.  The armored pet WILL win, everytime, with a good 10% life left.  Better yet, give it summoned Foci too.  you can add 120 AC and 120 hp to a pet with the items summonable by a 54 mage.  The hp left on the armored one should be closer to 15-20% then.<br>
<br>
Makes a big difference. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arhallia>Arhallia</A> at: 11/5/02 7:01:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fashionmagician>FashionMagician</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/02 7:35:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: wrong pet</span><hr size=1> I thought that summoned armor made no difference on pets either.  However, you may wish to take the armor out of the bag and hand the individual pieces to the pet. THEN the pet will equipt the armor.  If you just summon and hand bag to pet you get nada.  Some other info...<br>
<br>
49 fire pet, no armor or weapons, kills Seafury Cyclops and has less than 20% health left.<br>
<br>
Same pet with summoned plate, 2 Summoned Sword of Runes, kills Seafury Cyclops and has over 80% health left.<br>
<br>
In both cases, pet had BO3 buff.<br>
<br>
There is a big diference between armored and unarmored pets.  So, unless you are a die hard chain caster.. summon some armor for Jebober please....<br>
<br>
 <p><B>Zress</B> <BR>
<B>Fashion Magician</B> <BR> <I> <B>"((POOF!)) Your in style!"</I> </B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 8:36:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: wrong pet</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately, a single (or even 2-3) fights is not enough to determine whether or not summoned armor makes much difference.  The parses that I did trying to figure this out was over 50 fights armored, and 50 without, and showed little difference with having armor post-50th level.<br>
<br>
I used 51 earth, 53 air, and 54 water in my tests.  They were all fighting seafuries.  Now, seafuries vary in level, so there was some variation in the results.  Overall, summoned armor seemed to make about a 5% difference in the ending percentage... i.e. armored would end up with about 5% more hp's than non-armored.<br>
<br>
I believe, although I haven't thoroughly tested it, that summoned armor does help lower level pets.  Giving a level 24 pet summoned plate, for example, seems to make a large difference in the damage that it takes.  Giving a 49 earth pet summoned plate has little effect.<br>
<br>
I also think that different pets gain different benefits from summoned armor.  My experience has shown that earth, for example, doesn't show much change, if any at all.  Air seems to show the largest difference, with fire and water about the same.<br>
<br>
Post-50, giving your pet summoned armor shows very little results. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showPrevMessage?topicID=795.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showNextMessage?topicID=795.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=795.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.threadControl?topicID=795.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=795.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=795.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician P